    {t:'ChromaDB',d:'The open-source vector database used by the TMC chatbot to store and retrieve knowledge base embeddings. File: /app/data/vector_db/chroma.sqlite3. In TMC: keys.md is co-indexed with public content.'},
    {t:'Context Overflow',d:'An attack technique that embeds adversarial instructions after a very long innocuous text, hoping the model loses track of its original instructions as context fills up.'},
    {t:'Conversation ID',d:'A unique identifier for a chat session in the TMC chatbot (GET /api/conversation/<id>). Subject to IDOR — any valid ID returns the full conversation history without ownership verification.'},
    {t:'Direct Injection',d:'A prompt injection attack where the adversarial instruction is embedded directly in the user\'s message to the model (as opposed to indirect injection via retrieved content).'},
    {t:'Embedding',d:'A numerical vector representation of text used for semantic search. TMC uses all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (384 dimensions) to encode knowledge base documents for retrieval.'},
    {t:'Excessive Agency',d:'OWASP LLM06. An AI system has too much autonomy, permissions, or functionality. In TMC: the agent can close tickets, escalate them, and offer discounts with no authentication check.'},
    {t:'IDOR',d:'Insecure Direct Object Reference. Accessing another user\'s data by manipulating a reference (ticket number, conversation ID) without the server verifying ownership. TMC\'s ticket IDOR: any ticket number in chat returns full details.'},
    {t:'Indirect Injection',d:'Prompt injection delivered via data the model retrieves (documents, search results, emails) rather than via the user\'s direct message. In TMC: malicious instructions embedded in knowledge base documents.'},
    {t:'Jailbreak',d:'A prompt engineering technique that bypasses a model\'s safety guardrails by assigning an alternative persona (DAN, Opposite Mode, Chaos Mode) that the model adopts without restrictions.'},
    {t:'keys.md',d:'The intentionally vulnerable knowledge base file at knowledge_base/development/keys.md. Contains fake-but-realistic OpenAI API keys, AWS credentials, Stripe keys, JWT secret, Redis password, database connection strings, and admin credentials. Co-indexed with public product manuals in ChromaDB.'},
    {t:'known_issues.md',d:'The internal security vulnerability disclosure document at knowledge_base/development/known_issues.md. Documents the vector database credential leakage vulnerability and its attack vectors. Also co-indexed in the public vector DB.'},
